  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clothing 200 people sleeping rough this Christmas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Today one in five people are living in poverty in the UK. The nature of poverty has changed over time, so the ways we tackle poverty must change too.  Our society has a shared responsibility to work together to solve this problem.  This project will provide 200 people sleeping rough or living in poverty with vouchers to be redeemed at a charity shop in exchange for basic clothing to protect and keep them warm. Our vouchers  also financially benefit the charity shops cause. A win-win senario.</narrative>
  </description>
